{"questionId":"12632","questionHtml":"<p>Find the time, in years, for the population to decrease to 20 turtles.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"45 \\times {2^{ - t}} + 10 \\leqslant 20\">\n  <mn>45</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mi>t</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n  <mo>⩽</mo>\n  <mn>20</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for comparing correct expression involving 20 and their 45. Accept an equation.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t = 2.17\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2.17</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; (2.16992…)<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (A1)</strong></em><strong>(ft)</strong><em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;(C2)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Follow through from their part (a), but only if positive.<br><strong>Answer must be in years</strong>; do not accept months for the final <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em>.<em><strong> &nbsp;</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12632","referenceCode":"19M.1.SL.TZ2.T_13b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the time, in years, for the population to decrease to 20 turtles.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Prior learning","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}